From 2ebce24864c9f7637ea7cc1e89795e8d44824589 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Sep 2025 11:28:51 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP: mac80211: Reset ieee80211_link_sta to NULL after
 link removal

During link addition, ieee80211_link_sta in link_sta_info is assigned
from ieee80211_sta::deflink. However, after link removal, this pointer
is not being reset, leading to potential stale pointer access during
operations like NL80211_CMD_GET_STATION. This change ensures
ieee80211_link_sta is explicitly set to NULL after link removal
to prevent crashes and memory corruption.

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/sta_info.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/sta_info.c b/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
index 560c64a..64e981a 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/sta_info.c
@@ -430,6 +430,7 @@ static void sta_remove_link(struct sta_info *sta, unsigned int link_id,
 
 	RCU_INIT_POINTER(sta->link[link_id], NULL);
 	RCU_INIT_POINTER(sta->sta.link[link_id], NULL);
+	link_sta->sta = NULL;
 	if (alloc) {
 		sta_info_free_link(&alloc->info);
 		kfree_rcu(alloc, rcu_head);
-- 
